    "IntroductionThe mammalian neocortex is responsible for high-cognitive function and fine motor skills.",
    "The neocortex fulfills these functions through complicated networks of diverse neurons.",
    "Studies using rodents have established a basic framework of the neocortex, censused the transcriptomes of all the major cell types, and linked them to their physiological properties and principles of connection.",
    "Despite its augmented cognitive function, the primate neocortex shares the basic neuronal program with rodents.",
    "Accumulating evidence reveals the divergence between rodents and primates [1][2][3]."
